---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Callout from '../../components/Callout.astro';

export const title = "Cannabis Lab Testing Guide";
---

<Layout 
  title="Cannabis Lab Testing Guide | Maine Dispensary Guide" 
  description="Complete guide to cannabis product testing in Maine. Requirements, compliance, and working with licensed testing laboratories."
  heroImage="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1581091226825-a6a2a5aee158?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80&w=1200&h=400"
>
  <article>
    <div class="article-header">
      <h1>Cannabis Lab Testing Guide</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Understanding Maine's testing requirements for cannabis products</p>
    </div>

    <section>
      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>Testing isn't just a regulatory hurdle—it's your opportunity to prove your commitment to quality and safety. Maine's testing requirements exist to protect patients and customers while establishing your products as trustworthy and professional. When you embrace testing as part of your quality story, you set yourself apart from competitors who view it as merely a box to check. Before moving forward, familiarize yourself with the <a href="/guides/maine-dispensary-license/">licensing process</a> essential for success.</p>
    </section>

    <Callout title="Excellence in Compliance" type="success">
      Mastering this aspect of your business is a badge of professional excellence. It ensures longevity and demonstrates your commitment to the highest standards of the Maine cannabis industry.
    </Callout>


    <section>
      <h2>Why Testing Matters</h2>
      <p>Here's what proper testing accomplishes for your business:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Customer Safety</strong> — Verify products are free from harmful contaminants</li>
        <li><strong>Regulatory Compliance</strong> — Meet Maine OCP requirements for all products</li>
        <li><strong>Quality Verification</strong> — Confirm potency matches your <a href="/guides/maine-dispensary-packaging/">labeling</a></li>
        <li><strong>Brand Trust</strong> — Build customer confidence with transparent testing</li>
        <li><strong>Product Consistency</strong> — Ensure every batch meets your standards</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Testing Requirements</h2>
      <p>Under <a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/rules" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Maine OCP regulations</a>, all cannabis products must be tested by a licensed laboratory before sale. Here's what gets tested:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Potency</strong> — THC and CBD content verification</li>
        <li><strong>Microbial Contaminants</strong> — Bacteria, yeast, mold</li>
        <li><strong>Pesticides</strong> — Residue from growing operations</li>
        <li><strong>Heavy Metals</strong> — Lead, arsenic, mercury, cadmium</li>
        <li><strong>Residual Solvents</strong> — For concentrates and extracts</li>
        <li><strong>Moisture Content</strong> — Especially for flower products</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Working with Labs</h2>
      <p>Maine has licensed testing laboratories ready to serve your needs. When selecting a lab partner:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Verify they're licensed by Maine OCP</li>
        <li>Compare turnaround times</li>
        <li>Review pricing and sample requirements</li>
        <li>Ask about bulk testing discounts</li>
        <li>Ensure they test for all required analytes</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Compliance Tips</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Maintain proper sample chain of custody</li>
        <li>Keep detailed testing records for each batch</li>
        <li>Label products only after receiving passing test results</li>
        <li>Store testing documentation for inspection</li>
        <li>Establish relationships with multiple labs as backup</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Investment</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Category</th><th>Estimated Cost</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Testing (per sample)</td><td>$50-300+</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Monthly Testing Budget</td><td>$2,000-10,000+</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Compliance Documentation</td><td>$500-2,000</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section class="further-reading">
      <h2>Further Reading</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Maine Office of Cannabis Policy (OCP)</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/rules" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Maine Cannabis Testing Rules</a></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="disclaimer">
      <p><em>This is for informational purposes only and does not constitute legal or financial advice. Consult with qualified professionals.</em></p>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  article { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .article-header { margin-bottom: 2rem; padding-bottom: 1.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .subtitle { font-size: 1.25rem; color: var(--color-text-light); }
  section { margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  section h2, section h3 { margin-top: 1.5rem; }
  section h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
  table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 1rem 0; }
  th, td { padding: 0.75rem; text-align: left; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  th { background: var(--color-background); }
  ul { padding-left: 1.5rem; }
  li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .disclaimer { background: #fff3cd; border: 1px solid #ffc107; padding: 1rem; border-radius: 0.5rem; font-size: 0.875rem; margin-top: 2rem; }
  .further-reading { background: rgba(88, 129, 87, 0.05); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 1rem; margin-top: 3rem; }
  .further-reading h2 { margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.25rem; }
</style>
